<h3 style="margin-bottom: 0cm;" class="western" align="CENTER"><u>Guinness, Real Ale and Whisky Appreciation Society</u></h3><p style="margin-bottom: 0cm;" class="western" align="CENTER"><img src="http://www.dur.ac.uk/butler.jcr/application/views/involved/img/upload/009.jpg" width="243" height="243"><br /></p><p style="text-decoration: none; margin-bottom: 0cm;" class="western" align="JUSTIFY">If you're the kind of person who likes sitting down at the end of the day with a nice pint of ale, a measure of whisky or perhaps a reliable Guinness, then the GRAW (Guinness, Real Ale and Whisky) society is the place for you!</p><p style="text-decoration: none; margin-bottom: 0cm;" class="western" align="JUSTIFY"><br /></p><p style="text-decoration: none; margin-bottom: 0cm;" class="western" align="JUSTIFY">We will be holding regular meetings at Butler and Ustinov, where we provide ales and whiskies for people to taste and compare: a great chance to meet people and relax after a long week of work. We also organise socials where we go to a few pubs and, well, socialise!</p><p style="text-decoration: none; margin-bottom: 0cm;" class="western" align="JUSTIFY"><br /></p><p style="text-decoration: none; margin-bottom: 0cm;" class="western" align="JUSTIFY">This year will also see some tasting sessions from local breweries, and if there's enough interest, a couple of brewery visits as well...</p><p style="text-decoration: none; margin-bottom: 0cm;" class="western" align="JUSTIFY"><br /></p><p style="text-decoration: none; margin-bottom: 0cm;" class="western" align="JUSTIFY">Whether you're an established ale/whisky fan, or are looking to try something a little different, the GRAW society is a friendly and laid back place to be.</p><p style="text-decoration: none; margin-bottom: 0cm;" class="western" align="JUSTIFY"><br /></p><p style="text-decoration: none; margin-bottom: 0cm;" class="western" align="JUSTIFY">A year's membership is only Â£3 to go towards the cost of buying ale and whisky for the taster meetings, and really helps us to run the society; anyone interested in joining please contact the society president Owen Franklin or join our Facebook group at <a href="http://www.facebook.com/group.php?gid=133365263341370">www.facebook.com/group.php?gid=133365263341370</a>; the more the merrier!<br /></p><p style="text-decoration: none; margin-bottom: 0cm;" class="western" align="JUSTIFY"><br /></p>